    ns1:identificador "[START]" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Press [START] to execute the program." .

ns1:TeclaStop a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    ns1:identificador "[STOP]" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Repositioning may be interrupted (using the [STOP] key) to select other axes." .

ns1:TeclaTabulacion a ns1:Componente ;
    rdfs:label "Tecla de tabulación"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "The tab key moves the cursor to the next field of the active menu." .

ns1:Tecla_CANCEL a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "CANCEL key"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "the “CANCEL” softkey cancels the execution of the block while keeping the programmed machining conditions" .

ns1:Tecla_ENTER a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "ENTER key"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "The [ENTER] key restores from the history the block selected with the cursor and insert it in the edit line." .

ns1:Tecla_RESET a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "RESET key"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "The [RESET] key cancels the execution of the block and resets the CNC to its initial conditions." .

ns1:Tecla_START a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "START key"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "The [START] key executes the block currently displayed on the editing line." .

ns1:Tecla_STOP a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "STOP key"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "The [STOP] key interrupts the execution of the block." .

ns1:Tecla_UP_DOWN a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "[][] keys"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "use the [][] keys to pop-up the history and scroll it." .

ns1:Teclado a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    rdfs:label "Teclado"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Function keys. Softkeys. F1 Keys F1 through F12 select the options of the softkey menus. Browsing keys. NEXT key. NEXT OEM configurable table. FOCUS key. FOCUS It is used to switch between the different windows of the screen. BACK key. BACK On the horizontal softkey menu, it may be used to go from a softkey submenu up to the previous menu. Help key. HELP key. HELP Display CNC help. Work modes. Automatic mode. AUTO Jog mode. MANUAL EDISIMU mode. EDIT MDI/MDA mode. MDI User tables (zero offsets, fixtures and TABLES arithmetic parameters). Tool and magazine table. TOOLS Utilities mode. UTILITIES Configurable mode. CUSTOM OEM configurable table. Browsing keys. Main menu. MAIN MENU Changing the state of an icon. In the MC/TC mode, it toggles between the standard and the auxiliary screens. Keys to move the cursor. The arrow keys move the cursor one position to the left, right, up or down. The previous-page or next-page keys show the previous or next page at the part-program or PLC program editor. The home and end keys move the cursor the beginning or end of the line. The tab key moves the cursor to the next field of the active menu. Editing keys. Delete. Delete. DEL Insert or overwrite. INS Escape key, to cancel the current action ESC without assuming the changes. Key to validate commands, data and ENTER program blocks of the editor. Recover data. RECALL Calculator (*). CALC (*) The calculator key is not available on all keyboards." .

ns1:TecladoCNC1 a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    ns1:compuestoPor ns1:TeclaBrowsing1,
        ns1:TeclaEditing1,
        ns1:TeclaFunction1,
        ns1:TeclaHelp1,
        ns1:TeclaWorkModes1 ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Lámina de iconografía del teclado con pictogramas de teclas y grupos: Function keys (F1–F12/Softkeys), Browsing keys (MAIN MENU, NEXT, FOCUS, BACK), Help, Work modes (AUTO, MANUAL, EDIT, MDI, TABLES, TOOLS, UTILITIES, CUSTOM), y Editing keys (DEL, INS, ESC, ENTER, RECALL, CALC). Cada icono aparece en un recuadro con su rótulo y una breve leyenda funcional, estableciendo una codificación visual consistente para localizar acciones en la HMI." .

ns1:TeclasJOG a ns1:InterfazUsuario ;
    ns1:identificador "JOG keys" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Jog the axes with the handwheels or with the JOG keys." .

ns1:Tool a ns1:Parametro ;
    rdfs:label "Tool"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Tool. | T | 1 Press [T] on the alphanumeric keyboard. 2 Enter the tool to be selected. |  | 3 Press [START] to assume the entered value or [ESC] to cancel the operation."@en .

ns1:ToolCalibration a ns1:TareaMantenimiento ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Tool calibration. --- Palpado en torno con sonda de mesa; se resaltan lados activos “K”, distancia de seguridad “B” y velocidades de palpado." .

ns1:ToolChangeStep a ns1:TareaMantenimiento ;
    rdfs:label "Tool change step" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "press [START] to execute the tool change (if [ENTER] is pressed, the CNC will only show the tool data)" .

ns1:ToolInspection a ns1:TareaMantenimiento ;
    ns1:identificador "Tool inspection" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "After activating tool inspection, it is possible to jog the axes using the jog keyboard, act upon the master spindle of the channel from the operator panel and execute blocks from the MDI/MDA mode.",
        "Begin tool inspection. Tool inspection may be accessed from the vertical softkey menu only when the execution of the program has been interrupted ([STOP] key). After activating tool inspection, it is possible to jog the axes using the jog keyboard, act upon the master spindle of the channel from the operator panel and execute blocks from the MDI/MDA mode. Execute blocks in MDI/MDA mode. Any program block may be executed in MDI/MDA mode. The conditions when entering the MDI/MDA mode will be those of the interruption point; i.e. the CNC maintains the history of active G and M functions, feedrate, spindle speed, tool and other commands that were programmed. However, the CNC treats certain functions and commands (type of movements, radius compensation, etc.) differently. Refer to the operating manual. In general, all the changes made in MDI/MDA mode are kept active when resuming the program after tool inspection except the following functions that are restored at the time of interruption; type of interpolation (G00, G01, G02, G03, G33 or G63), G90/G91 function or #MCS function. Repositioning the axes and the spindle. To complete the tool inspection and before resuming the execution of the program, the spindle turning direction must be restored and the axes repositioned.",
        "Execute blocks in MDI/MDA mode. Any program block may be executed in MDI/MDA mode.",
        "However, the CNC treats certain functions and commands (type of movements, radius compensation, etc.) differently.",
        "In general, all the changes made in MDI/MDA mode are kept active when resuming the program after tool inspection except the following functions that are restored at the time of interruption; type of interpolation (G00, G01, G02, G03, G33 or G63), G90/G91 function or #MCS function.",
        "Repositioning the axes and the spindle. To complete the tool inspection and before resuming the execution of the program, the spindle turning direction must be restored and the axes repositioned.",
        "The conditions when entering the MDI/MDA mode will be those of the interruption point; i.e. the CNC maintains the history of active G and M functions, feedrate, spindle speed, tool and other commands that were programmed.",
        "Tool inspection may be accessed from the vertical softkey menu only when the execution of the program has been interrupted ([STOP] key).",
        "When switching to execution mode (after pressing the softkey), the CNC goes into tool inspection to reposition the axes, modify program conditions, etc." .

